 ]
 //Sensitivity list 
 
 it contains signals that affect outputs.
 
 Blocking Vs Non-Blocking
 
 
 Blocking ----symbol: =-------
 
 exectued sequentially.
 
 Blocks next statements until it is executed.
 
 LHS is updated after reading RHS of the same statement. 
 Describes Multi-level combinational logic
 
 if not triggere, it is uninitialized.
 
 Non-Blocking ----------<=------------
 
 Executed in parallel
 RHS is read immediatey, but updating LHS starts after all reads are scheduled.
 Describe FLIP-FLop assignment at the saem time regardless to the order or the dependence.
 
 if not triggered, it keep the last value.
 
 
 
